here are the forces that defense secretary 
dick cheney said will be deployed both from europe and the united 
states for operation desert shield in the persian gulf 
army troops from germany 
the 7th corps headquarters from stuttgart the 1st armored 
division ansbach the 3rd armored division frankfurt a 
brigadesize unit from the 2nd armored division garlstedt the 2nd 
armored cavalry regiment nuernberg and the 2nd corps support 
command stuttgart 
from the united states 
the 1st infantry division mechanized from fort riley kan 
cheney said various units to support and service the additional 
ground forces would be sent from the united states and europe 
cheney said the navy will send three additional aircraft carrier 
battle groups plus escort ships he did not identify the carriers 
he said the uss missouri battleship also would be sent with escort 
vessels as well as amphibious group three from san diego calif 
the marine corps will be sending the 2nd marine expeditionary 
force from camp lejeune nc the 5th marine expeditionary brigade 
from camp pendleton calif and the maritime prepositioning ship 
squadron one from norfolk va 
he said additional air force units may be tapped 
there clearly will be a need to call up further reserve units 
and we will also will be calling up for the first time combat units 
of the army national guard cheney said 
specifically he said the units would include three national 
guard units the 48th infantry brigade mechanized from georgia the 
155th armored brigade from mississippi and the 256th infantry 
brigade mechanized from louisiana 
they will be called up in the period ahead be given 
substantial additional workup here at home and then a decision will 
be made about whether or not they will be deployed overseas 
cheney said 
its conceivable that if we deem them combatready that they 
would be deployed as part of operation desert shield he said 
its also possible that they would be deployed here to fill in 
behind units that we take out of the continental united states and 
shipped to saudi arabia and the gulf 
