senators 
theyd seen bushs success in 1988 when he was elected president 
after telling the nation read my lips no new taxes 
but this was 1990 and taxes suddenly appeared on the white house 
table in the election schuette martin and schneider were wiped 
out sen paul simon beat martin by 30 percentage points sen 
claiborne pell topped schneider by 24 points sen carl levin 
outpolled schuette by 16 
 
