the food and drug administration is warning 
consumers against taking an illegally marketed and possibly 
dangerous drug used for strength training and body building 
the fda said thursday that it had received reports of more than 
30 people in california florida and georgia becoming ill after 
taking ghb or gamma hydroxybutyric acid 
the drug is also called sodium oxybate and gamma hydroxybutyrate 
sodium 
the fda said ghb can cause nausea and vomiting severe 
respiratory problems seizures and coma 
ghb is sold as powder or granules through mail order outlets 
health food stores gyms and fitness centers it is promoted for 
strength training body building weight loss and as a replacement 
for ltryptophan 
ltryptophan a food supplement used as a sleep aid and for 
depression and weight control was ordered off the market last 
march when it was linked to an outbreak of a rare blood disorder 
called eosinophiliamyalgia syndrome 
ghb is being evaluated in approved clinical trials as a 
treatment for narcolepsy a sleep disorder 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
rules proposed by the federal communications 
commission would require all telephone companies to provide service 
to hearing and speechimpaired callers by mid1993 
the commissions 50 vote thursday set into motion rules to 
fulfill the communications provisions of the americans with 
disabilities act of 1990 
the act which president bush signed in july requires that the 
nations 26 million hearing and speechimpaired individuals have 
access to phone company relay services that allow them to 
communicate with hearing callers 
impaired callers typically punch a keyboard connected with a 
telephone operator who then relays the message either 
electronically to another impaired person or verbally to a hearing 
caller 
the provisions cover intrastate and interstate calls and states 
will be allowed to establish prices for intrastate services with 
fcc oversight 
the fcc must establish rules within a year and phone companies 
must meet those provisions by july 26 1993 
the proposal requires among other things 24hour service 
seven days a week with rates commensurate with those of 
functionally equivalent voice communications services 
relay operators may not refuse calls limit their length or 
reveal or alter their contents 
</TEXT>
