leaders of 55 million catholics support un economic sanctions 
against iraq and condemn iraqi aggression and the taking of 
hostages after iraq invaded kuwait on aug 2 
but ethical considerations should not be ignored or neglected 
in a focus on simple military and geopolitical considerations 
mahony said 
is the damage to be inflicted and the costs incurred by war 
proportionate to the objectives to be achieved by taking up arms 
he wrote will war with iraq leave the people of kuwait the 
middle east and the world better or worse off 
we understand that a strong military presence can give 
credibility to a vigorous pursuit of nonviolent solutions to the 
crisis he said but he added that he was concerned that the 
pressure to use military force may grow as efforts to pursue 
nonviolent options almost inevitably become difficult complex 
and slow 
