<TEXT>
king birendra whose grip on absolute 
power was shaken by a springtime prodemocracy uprising today 
enacted a constitution reducing his powers 
the new document establishes a constitutional monarchy and 
declares the himalayan nation a multiparty democracy 
it abolishes the old system under which political parties were 
banned and the king ruled with a nonpartisan legislature that 
routinely approved measures favored by the monarch 
i feel very much elated on such a historic occasion for which 
the people have been aspiring and have laid down their lives 
prime minister krishna prasad bhattarai told a news conference 
the draft of a proposed constitution was completed two months 
ago but enactment bogged down in a tugofwar between the palace 
and bhattarais fledging government over how much power the king 
should retain 
bhattarai said the king agreed to act in the same fashion as 
britains constitutional monarchy 
he said general elections will be held sometime between 
midapril and early may next year 
in a message broadcast live on national radio and television 
birendra said the new constitution will help to forge the people 
in a bond of unity and advance the cause of multiparty democracy in 
a constitutional monarchy 
he said the document takes effect immediately 
the adoption of the new constitution culminates a prodemocracy 
campaign that began in late winter with weeks of strikes and street 
demonstrations by doctors lawyers students and the longbanned 
political parties 
the turning point came on april 6 when police opened fire as 
200000 demonstrators marched to the royal palace at least 72 
people were killed according to official accounts witnesses put 
the death toll at more than 300 
shortly afterward the king caved in to pressure and asked 
bhattarai a top leader of the nepali congress party to form an 
interim government until elections could be held in the spring of 
1991 
the nepali congress party and all other political parties were 
banned by birendras father king mahendra when he ended an 
18month experiment with democracy in december 1960 
birendra was crowned king in 1972 when his father died he is 
the latest monarch in the 223yearold shah dynasty 
the new constitution declares nepal a hindu and constitutional 
monarchical kingdom the buddhist and christian minorities had 
sought to have nepal declared a secular state 
hindus comprise 90 percent of nepals 17 million people moslems 
make up 5 percent while christians comprise 3 percent most of the 
others are buddhists 
under the new constitution nepal will have a twohouse 
parliament consisting of a policymaking house of representatives 
and an upper house called the national council 
all 205 members of the house of representatives and 35 of the 45 
members of the national council will be elected the remaining 10 
members of the upper house will be appointed by the king 
