<DOCNO> AP901109-0089 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
indias new prime minister chandra 
shekhar is the aging angry young man of indian politics 
leftleaning since his university days the 63yearold 
politician tapped for the job friday has long advocated social and 
economic justice for indias masses most of indias top political 
leaders have 
few have had much luck changing things in a country of 880 
million people where fewer than half can read and write and the 
average annual income is barely 300 
but chandra shekhar who seems to be perpetually scowling 
through his saltandpepper beard knows a little more about such 
things than most of his fellow players at the top ranks of the 
national political game 
he was born in the village of ibrahimpatti near the borders of 
uttar pradesh and bihar state 460 miles southeast of new delhi 
the region is geographically remote but politically in the 
center of northern indias hindu heartland it has produced all of 
the countrys prime ministers 
years ago chandra shekhar told an interviewer he was the first 
educated man from his village of 1000 people my mother is 
illiterate my father too is hardly literate he said 
but like all of indias prime ministers he came from an upper 
caste in the complex hindu social system which automatically 
confers pride and privilege if not wealth 
chandra shekhar rejected this hedropped his familys surname 
of singh which made him instantly recognizable as a member of the 
thakur or landlord caste he now goes only by his first 
name chandra shekhar which is written as two words 
he studied political science at allahabad university in uttar 
pradesh state and joined obscure socialist groups 
in 1967 he switched to the congress party that produced indias 
first prime minister jawaharlal nehru and the prime ministerial 
dynasty of nehrus daughter indira gandhi and her son rajiv 
gandhi 
chandra shekhar was briefly a stalwart of mrs gandhi 
supporting her decision to nationalize banks and abolish the 
maharajahs privy purses but he broke with her as she moved deeper 
into authoritarian rule culminating in the state of emergency from 
1975 to 1977 when she suspended civil rights and elections 
he was one of thousands of political leaders jailed by mrs 
gandhi during the emergency much of his 21 months in prison was 
spent in solitary confinement 
when mrs gandhi lifted the emergency and overconfidently 
called elections in 1977 chandra shekhar was among the founders of 
the janata party that defeated her but the prime ministers job 
went to someone else chandra shekhar became the partys president 
less than two years later the janata government fell part in 
internal bickering 
history looks like its ready to repeat itself except this 
time the party broke apart before the government did 
chandra shekhar remained president of the janata party until 
1988 when it disbanded to become a major component of the janata 
dal party a collection of politicians drawn together by little 
more than their dislike of rajiv gandhi 
he joined the janata dal led by singh the prime minister whose 
11monthold government was ousted in a parliament vote wednesday 
only two days before the vote chandra shekhar led a breakaway 
faction of the janata dal party in opposing singh 
chandra shekhar calls his splinter group the janata dal 
socialist which counts between 50 and 60 members in the 522seat 
policymaking lower house of parliament for the moment at least 
he has the support of his longtime foe rajiv gandhi and gandhis 
195member congress party 
how long chandra shekhar can keep the prime ministers job is 
questionable gandhi after a year as opposition leader is waiting 
in the wings for yet another noncongress party government to 
disintegrate if the congress party withdraws support it is 
unlikely chandra shekhar could find sufficient support elsewhere to 
survive 
until the current political maneuvering chandra shekhar was 
bestknown in india for the 2500mile walk he did over six months 
in 1983 
he traveled from indias southernmost tip to new delhi saying 
he wanted to see firsthand and dramatize the plight of the 
countrys downtrodden it was a tactic borrowed from indias 
beloved independence leader and apostle of nonviolence mohandas k 
gandhi the mahatma or great soul 
but chandra shekhars padayatra or foot travel 
produced little more than publicity for him 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

