<TEXT>
belgium has ordered an investigation 
into the activities of a secret group formed during the cold war to 
fight potential communist invaders in several nato countries an 
official said friday 
defense minister guy coeme said his government suspected the 
littleknown group might be linked to a series of murders around 
brussels between 1983 asnd 1985 
the inquiry was launched after speculation was raised in italy 
that the italian branch of the organization known as operation 
gladio might have orchestrated rightwing terrorism 
the anticommunist groups were organized in the 1950s and 
operated in several other countries of the north atlantic treaty 
organization including greece and portugal 
they set up information and communication networks and also had 
a special sabotage division to be put to se in case of a communist 
invasion officials of both italy and belgium said 
cells of the secret network were active in portugal during the 
1950s to defend the rightist government of dictator antonio 
oliveira salazar according to a radio report in lisbon on friday 
the greek defense minister yannis varvitsiotis said friday the 
cia helped set up a similar network in greece in 1955 to organize a 
guerrilla war against any communist invader known as operation 
sheepskin it was dismantled by 1988 he said 
prime minister wilfried martens who has headed the belgian 
government almost continuously since 1979 said he was never 
informed of the existence of the belgian arm of the group which he 
said was set up by the belgian military 
it was not an official network martens told a news 
conference friday 
he said however that nato knew of the groups activities 
although they were not an official part of the organization 
this network is a complete anachronism we favor abolishing 
it martens said 
italy has asked nato to investigate whether the secret groups 
are still needed 
nato spokesman florent swijsen declined comment on the groups 
saying natos established practice on matters of military 
secrecy is not to provide information or to comment in any way 
coeme said operation gladio cell officials met in brussels two 
weeks ago to see whether it was still useful to have this kind of 
service considering the growing eastwest cooperation 
in italy speculation abounds that the group was involved in 
rightwing terrorism during the 1970s and 1980s however italian 
premier giulio andreotti said thursday he had no evidence that any 
crimes were committed in operation gladio 
belgium is investigating whether it was involved in a series of 
supermarket attacks and robberies that left at least 28 people dead 
between 1983 and 1985 
the attackers were always more bent on killing than stealing 
the violent incidents have often been linked by authorities to 
rightwing terrorism police have made little progress in the case 
