a cyanide leak into a river in the soviet 
republics of byelorussia and latvia has poisoned water supplies to 
several cities and caused at least two people to become ill 
officials said friday 
the leak into the daugava river apparently from a chemical 
weapons plant occurred sometime between oct 31 and nov 5 said 
authorities in the two republics 
they said officials of the plant which makes chemicals for use 
in chemical weapons never told them about the leak 
it is just the same as chernobyl we only learned that 
something went wrong when we saw fish floating belly up down the 
stream said latvian deputy prime minister ilmar bisher he 
referred to the 1983 nuclear power plant disaster in the nearby 
ukraine 
two men ate a fish and got minor poisoning we hope there 
will be no more cases said bisher head of a latvian commission 
investigating the leak 
