<TEXT>
the leading antianxiety drug has become the 
first medication approved for panic disorder officials said 
friday 
an estimated 3 million americans 1 percent to 2 percent of the 
population will suffer from panic disorder in their lifetimes 
for more than half of them it will disrupt their social and 
working lives 
the illness is characterized by repeated panic attacks in which 
a patient is struck by intense fear by avoiding situations 
associated with the attacks some sufferers become housebound or 
are unable to go outside alone 
symptoms of the attacks can include chest pain shortness of 
breath dizziness trembling and sweating nausea and abdominal 
distress the symptoms often mimic a heart attack which can lead 
to an incorrect diagnosis said officials of the upjohn co which 
makes xanax 
the food and drug administration first approved xanax in 1981 
for the treatment for clinical anxiety and anxiety associated with 
depression 
common side effects of xanax in panic disordersufferers include 
sedation and fatigue but as is the case with anxiety treatment 
those reactions eased when the dose was reduced or as the 
medication was continued upjohn said 
however because higher doses of xanax may be needed for longer 
periods of time to treat panic disorder the fda was concerned 
about the potential for dependency on the drug 
at higher doses and longer duration there is potential for 
physical dependency on xanax and withdrawal symptoms when the drug 
is stopped or reduced too rapidly said fda spokeswoman eva 
kemper 
because of that possibility xanax must be withdrawn gradually 
and under a physicians supervision she said 
a biochemical malfunctioning in the brain is believed to cause 
panic attacks the company said xanax known generically as 
alprazolam can block the attacks by interacting with several 
different systems in the brain 
upjohn studied alprazolam as a treatment for the disorder in a 
twophase study that involved more than 1700 patients in more than 
14 countries the company said 
</TEXT>
