germany marked the anniversary of the berlin 
walls collapse friday but some among the shivering crowds at 
ceremonies said the joy of the event had faded because of pressing 
economic problems 
friday was also the 52nd anniversary of the nocturnal rampage 
against jewish homes businesses and synagogues that foreshadowed 
