<TEXT>
france commemorated the 20th anniversary of charles 
de gaulles death friday with a respect and affection that eluded 
the former war hero and president in his final years 
throughout the country religious services exhibitions 
symposiums television programs and plays paid tribute to de gaulle 
as leader of french resistance to nazi occupation and founder of 
the current constitutional system with its strong president 
in contrast to his sometimes tempestuous presidency from 1959 to 
1969 de gaulle now is admired by frenchmen of all political 
persuasions 
a poll published thursday in the newspaper le monde said 84 
percent of the respondents believe de gaulles record in office was 
positive 
the nearuniversal admiration contrasts with the generals last 
years when students and workers rioted in the streets 
de gaulles unpopularity culminated in a humiliating defeat at 
the polls in 1969 and drove him from the presidency 
nineteen months later on nov 9 1970 while playing solitaire 
at his home in colombeylesdeuxeglises de gaulle suffered a 
ruptured aneurism and died 
the following afternoon his son philippe went on television to 
announce general de gaulle is dead france is a widow 
only his family close wartime colleagues and villagers attended 
his funeral on nov 12 while dozens of heads of state attended 
ceremonies at notre dame cathedral in paris 
today it is hard to find de gaulle bashers one exception is 
recoursfrance helpfrance an organization of former french 
residents of north africa many of whom lost everything when france 
embarked on decolonization 
for the french from algeria he will forever be regarded as 
the man who betrayed mislead and abandoned us without ever 
pronouncing a single word of compassion for our tragic exodus 
the organization said in a statement friday 
at the start of the algerian revolution de gaulle pledged to 
maintain french rule he later granted independence to end the 
bloodshed 
many ardent leftists have become de gaulle admirers regis 
debray a former adviser to socialist president francois 
mitterrand described de gaulle as the last great man of the 19th 
century and the first great man of the 21st 
in a new book a demain de gaulle tomorrow de gaulle 
debray once a leading exponent of guerrilla warfare and a 
champion of the late che guevara paid homage to the generals 
traditionalist values 
mitterrand himself paid tribute friday sending his army chief 
to lay a wreath at de gaulles tomb in colombeylesdeuxeglises 
exhibitions and documentaries abound including one on de 
gaulles manipulation of the media for political purposes alain 
peyrefitte de gaulles information minister has said de gaulle 
himself edited television newscasts and used the media as an 
instrument of power 
this month also marks the first time de gaulles life and 
achievements have been presented in fiction 
based on a forgotten scenario by william faulkner one of de 
gaulles most fervent admirers director denys granierdeferre has 
made a tv movie recounting the war years 
a lesserknown side of de gaulle is depicted in villa luco 
a play about de gaulles secret visit to elderly ailing marshall 
philippe petain condemned to life imprisonment for collaborating 
with the nazis 
this year also marks the 100th anniversary of de gaulles birth 
and the 50th anniversary of his famed radio appeal from london for 
frenchmen to resist the nazis 
