yen 7700 said hideji matsuda of toshibas new media 
division 
hdtv offers extremely detailed images digital sound and wider 
cinemastyle screen proportions until now the equipment was aimed 
at a small number of professionals and was large heavy and 
expensive 
hdtv adaptors for example weighed as much as 209 pounds and 
filled a small cabinet but new models displayed this week by many 
companies weigh as little as 13 pounds and are the size of a large 
cable tv adaptor 
in europe companies have developed a competing hdtv system that 
is not expected to be brought to market until 1992 
in the united states government officials are still debating 
what technical standards to set for hdtv and how it should be 
broadcast 
unlike japan where hdtv signals are broadcast directly from a 
satellite to viewers homes the us federal communications 
commission is exploring a simulcast system in which current 
landbased television stations would broadcast normal programs on 
their present channels and hdtv information on separate channels 
japan broadcasting corp the public television network 
currently broadcasts one hour of hdtv satellite programming a day 
fulltime broadcasting is scheduled to start in early 1992 
although japans hdtv system is not compatibile with current 
equipment with the new adaptors anyone with a regular television 
will be able to tune in hdtv programs although with regular 
picture quality 
hdtv monitors announced by sony matsushita nec toshiba and 
other companies can receive regular japanese tv broadcasts 
