transition period to transfer the bases to full philippine control 
and that the timeframe could vary depending on the installation 
on thursday he said the united states would like to maintain 
access to some of these facilities and to maintain a small residual 
american military presence in the country similar to the agreements 
we have with many other countries around the world 
any new agreement must be ratified by twothirds of the 
23member philippine senate where opposition to the installations 
is strong 
opinion surveys show most filipinos support the bases but many 
influential figures in government academic circles and media 
