carved two passages in the 11foothigh concrete in the shapes of a 
man and a woman so people can pass through freely 
reagan led dignitaries in walking through the openings in the 
wall which is a stark gray on the side that once faced east they 
emerged on the old west side adorned with bright graffiti the 
word unwahr german for untruth appears frequently on the 
wall which has been placed near a bronze statue of churchill 
ms sandys whose sculptures have been displayed in europe and 
at the united nations said she was accustomed to working in 
marble 
thirtytwo feet of concrete created quite a challenge 
unyielding slabs of concrete steeped as they are in heroism and 
history she told the audience 
the sculpture was dedicated on the oneyear anniversary of the 
fall of the wall and more than three years after reagan during a 
berlin visit called on soviet leader mikhail gorbachev to tear 
down this wall 
churchill first invoked the image of an iron curtain to describe 
growing soviet influence during a speech at westminster on march 5 
1946 
from stettin in the baltic to trieste in the adriatic an iron 
curtain has descended across the continent he said 
today we come full circle from those anxious times reagan 
said out of one mans speech was born a new western resolve 
some of those attending the ceremony friday had been on hand for 
churchills speech 44 years earlier 
raymond miller of fulton drove the towns mayor in the parade 
for churchill and said it was one of the highlights of his 64 
years 
im real thrilled about being part of history he predicted 
back in 1946 miller said 
</TEXT>
