the american consumer gives little promise of 
providing much help as the economy and wall street struggle into 
the last few weeks of a difficult year 
surveys that seek to measure sentiment among the shopping public 
show a pronounced mood of caution heading into the traditional peak 
season for business at the nations retail stores 
even if consumers were inclined to come riding to the rescue 
analysts say all the economic evidence shows them low on 
ammunition in the form of money to spend 
personal income growth is slowing markedly observed david 
