tashjian an analyst with seidler amdec securities inc in los 
angeles theyre not going to buy 100 electronic toys for their 
kids not this year 
analysts said shoppers will be looking harder for bargains and 
waiting longer for price reductions than in past years 
theyre going to be busy spending fewer dollars said daniel 
barry an analyst with kidder peabody amp co 
consumers cut spending as the economy weakened and after the 
iraqi invasion of kuwait raised the specter of war inflating 
prices of gasoline and home heating oil 
the first items crossed off shopping lists were socalled 
