due to an increase in acreage average yields were forecast at 298 
hundredweight per acre down one hundredweight from 1989 
drought in north dakota and minnesota cut into production 
potential for the third straight year the report said maine 
farmers were hit by heavy october rains followed by hard freezes 
late in the month that virtually shut down harvest operations 
