cut at the newspaper but that he was hopeful the number would be so 
small that it could be absorbed through attrition rather than 
layoffs 
there is a feeling that as in practically every other business 
in america we should tighten our belts deford said in a 
telephone interview 
deford denied that the newspaper was in serious financial 
trouble as it tries to become the first national sports daily in 
america its just a matter of belttightening he said 
on thursday a source who spoke on condition of anonymity said 
the sunday issue was being discontinued because circulation on 
sundays has amounted to only about 80 percent of that on weekdays 
and it has proven harder to distribute the paper on sundays than on 
weekdays 
the national has been published six days a week sunday through 
friday since it was launched on jan 31 
