the vast majority of top economists in a 
monthly survey believe a recession will begin before years end 
but most predict it will be brief and relatively mild a prominent 
economic newsletter reported friday 
blue chip economic indicators said 80 percent of the 55 
economists in its survey feel a downturn will start before the end 
of 1990 another 5 percent said the slump would start in 1991 
it now seems very likely that americas longest peacetime 
expansion is about to come to an end wrote blue chip editor 
robert j eggert of eggert economic enterprises inc in sedona 
ariz 
