to be relatively brief and relatively minor boskin told the 
american council for capital formation here 
the blue chip survey found threefourths of the respondents 
expect any downturn to last no more than two or three quarters 
an even larger majority 82 percent anticipate that the 
recession will be relatively mild the newsletter said 
because of the predicted slump the newsletters masthead was 
printed in red ink for the first time since the last recession a 
warning that economic growth may drop below zero a recession 
generally is defined as two consecutive quarterly economic 
declines 
since the economy emerged from the july 1981november 1982 
downturn the blue chip banner has been either green or yellow 
green meant the economy was expanding above longrange growth 
potential of 3 percent while yellow warned that economic growth 
was lagging between zero and 29 percent 
