<TEXT>
toys r us which made its name and fortune by 
setting up shop in the burbs has finally moved into the big city 
the worlds largest toy retailer reached a new milestone last 
week with the opening of its first downtown branch in the united 
states a threelevel store in manhattans herald square just 
across from two big competitors macys flagship department store 
and lionel corps kiddie city 
the move represents a big opportunity for toys r us convenience 
for manhattanites who used to travel to suburbia for toys and a 
headache for stores that havent had this kind of competition 
before 
robert nakasone a toys r us vice chairman said the company was 
doing so well in the suburbs it felt for years that it didnt need 
to move into downtown locations 
we said why go ahead and do it he said friday the 
stores second day open 
but eventually toys r us realized manhattan was too lucrative a 
market to keep passing up nakasone said the company decided to 
open a toy store and a companion kids r us clothing store in the 
heart of the city 
the success of kiddie citys herald square store may well have 
been an inducement to toys r us to give manhattan a try 
until a few years ago if you wanted to buy toys in manhattan 
you had few choices there was fao schwarz on fifth avenue for the 
upper crust and department stores and a handful of small 
neighborhood stores for everyone else 
kiddie city was a trailblazer when it opened its herald square 
store several years ago it was a big success and lionel followed 
with two other stores in residential areas of manhattan 
toys r us which has more than 700 stores in the united states 
and overseas has branches in new york citys other four boroughs 
but before last week its only other downtown stores were in 
singapore and germany 
the site chosen by toys r us is the building known as herald 
center on broadway between 33rd and 34th streets it couldnt be 
more high profile it is smack in the middle of manhattans 
biggest shopping area directly across from macys 
the arrival of toys r us provides herald center with a chance at 
revival following a checkered history 
the building began retail life as a saks amp co branch known as 
saks 34th it was a poor cousin to the more famous saks fifth 
avenue 
saks closed the store about 30 years ago and it later became a 
discount retailer korvettes after korvettes folded in the 1970s 
the building became herald center a vertical mall that had few 
stores and few shoppers 
the building later was tied to former philippine president 
ferdinand marcos and his wife imelda it was sold at a 
courtordered auction recently and is being renovated with toys r 
us and kids r us as the malls centerpieces 
for toys r us moving into herald center required a revamping of 
the companys standard onestory configuration shelves had to be 
fit around pillars and columns and elevators and escalators had to 
be installed the total facelift cost more than 1 million 
nakasone said 
the herald square store also is more expensive to run 
with less stockroom space than other toys r us stores it will 
have be resupplied more often that means more trips to the 
companys new jersey warehouse and higher labor and fuel costs 
moving into manhattan also meant toys r us trucks had to be 
adapted to fit into the lincoln tunnel a key thoroughfare that 
connects new york and new jersey 
but to children its like any other toys r us outlet its 
stocked from floor to ceiling with dolls nintendo units and 
cartridges teenage mutant ninja turtles and bicycles 
to competitors toys r us poses a big threat 
macy has long touted itself as the place to go for christmas 
toys but the department store may find itself hardpressed to 
compete with the price and selection that shoppers will find just 
across the street 
kiddie city while carrying many toys also does not have as 
wide a selection as toys r us while toys r us had aisles of 
nintendo equipment and cartridges last week kiddie citys video 
games were tucked into a corner of the store 
fao schwarz could find it has lost some sales to its downtown 
rival because toys r us prices are lower 
for instance a popular baby doll called oopsie daisy so named 
because she falls down and cries costs 66 at fao schwarz and 
40 at toys r us teenage mutant ninja turtles figures that go for 
8 in fao schwarz were selling for 5 at toys r us 
but this doesnt mean a store like fao schwarz should close up 
shop the store appears to be downscaling somewhat it no longer 
features a 15000 junior ferrari in its catalog but still has 
100plus plush animals 300plus dolls and a fifth avenue cachet 
that no other toy store has 
nakasone appeared unconcerned about competition he noted toys r 
us competes with kiddie city in other markets 
he also did not appear worried about the effect that the 
weakened economy and the persian gulf crisis have had on the retail 
business while declining to project what toys r us sales will be 
this year nakasone predicted parents would still spend generously 
on toys 
we expect to have a good christmas he said 
</TEXT>
