government bond prices jumped friday as the 
market anticipated the federal reserve board would lower interest 
rates when it gathers next week traders said 
the price of the governments bellwether 30year bond climbed 
2932 point or about 906 per 1000 in face value its yield 
which falls when the bonds price rises slid to 862 percent from 
870 percent late thursday 
bond prices rose despite a government report showing wholesale 
prices soared 11 percent in october the third consecutive monthly 
advance boosted by rising food and energy prices 
the jump brought producerprice inflation for the first 10 
months of the year to a 7 percent annual rate sharply higher than 
1989s 49 percent rate and the worst since inflation soared at 
doubledigit rates in the early 1980s 
but the bond market took its cue from the socalled core 
inflation rate which doesnt include food and energy prices said 
bob sbarra a senior vice president at the investment firm carroll 
mcentee amp mcginley inc 
minus those factors inflation didnt change from september 
investors believe the feds open market committee will vote at a 
meeting tuesday to lower interest rates to counteract increasing 
signs that the economy is entering a recession traders said the 
flat core inflation rate also gives the fed more latitude to lower 
rates they added 
lower rates benefit fixedreturn securities such as bonds 
some traders are looking for a point reduction in the federal 
funds rate following the feds meeting that is the interest rate 
banks charge each other on overnight loans 
that belief prompted investors to buy government bonds friday 
bidding up the price said william pike a managing director in the 
government bondtrading department of manufacturers hanover trust 
co the government bond market is closed monday for veterans day 
pike said the market also was buoyed by a general sense of 
optimism sparked by lower oil and gold prices higher stock prices 
and the successful completion this week of the treasurys record 
quarterly refunding auction 
in the market for existing treasury bonds friday shortterm 
issues rose 332 point to 1132 intermediate maturities rose 1132 
point to point and longterm issues rose 2932 point to 3132 
point according to telerate inc a financial information service 
the movement of a point is equivalent to a change of 10 in the 
price of a bond with a 1000 face value 
