merely need to be less specific in the charges which allege that 
bonds were sold in ways not approved by the department 
on the other two counts prosecutors were more likely to add 
additional counts to add more detail he said 
keating and the others are accused of misleading investors and 
regulators about the safety of uninsured bonds sold to lincoln 
savings depositors about 250 million worth of junk bonds 
became worthless when lincoln and its parent company collapsed 
many elderly investors lost their life savings 
abbe lowell one of the defense attorneys said he did not think 
prosecutors would have much luck with the amended charges which 
must be filed with the court by nov 19 
let them try as they might they cannot create statutes where 
none exist lowell said 
he said he thought keating had been charged as the result of 
hysteria over the nations savings and loan crisis by wellmeaning 
but mistaken prosecutors 
i think that the district attorney is a little bit confused 
about who the wrongdoers are he said 
ito allowed to stand 20 counts alleging that bonds were sold to 
lincoln savings investors by means of untrue statements or 
omissions of material facts 
ito ordered the attorneys to return on dec 3 for another 
hearing the defense said they would pursue additional motions to 
dismiss the case at that time no matter how many charges are 
allowed to stand then 
