<TEXT>
mazda motor of america on friday recalled 
2708 rx7s because three of the sports cars may have defective 
airbags 
the automaker has been notified by airbag manufacturer trw that 
there might be three defective airbags among rx7s manufactured 
between nov 1 1989 and july 2 1990 said mazda spokesman bob 
marsocci 
theres a mechanism that senses when theres an impact and 
that module might be defective he said the recall was 
voluntary 
owners are being notified by mail to take their cars to mazda 
dealers for inspections if necessary the airbags will be replaced 
at no cost 
mazda said it was not aware of any injuries that have resulted 
from any defective airbags 
